		<div id="comment_body_64550273"><p>Sudo neither does one thing, nor does it do so well.  And has a pretty abysmal track record because of how it's implemented.<nobr> <wbr></nobr>..BTW, "unix philosophy" is *simplicity of implementation* over all else.  Even over correctness and (especially) consistency.</p><p>systemd's run0 uses the exact sort of process isolation that sshd uses, and most of what relies on has been part of core systemd since the beginning -- ya know, being able to launch commands as various users and clean up leftover messes afterwards.</p></div>
