		<div id="comment_body_64551205"><p>Your comment just proves the point. The STDIN/STDOUT/STDERR interface is really bad. It's freeform text with near zero consistency. Sometimes tools have special options to simplify or regularize the output, but often you have to use another text processing tool to parse it and extract the information you want.</p><p>The result is combinations that work, but which are brittle and rely on the tools never updating their output too much. Debugging is a pain as there is rarely any facility for error handling or even er<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
