	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64550433"><p>I do this now and it's not that hard, at least for text files that I edit which is usually all I care about versioning.</p><p>mkdir ~/.vi    # do this once<br>vi ~/bin/edit ; chmod 755 ~/bin/edit  # create this file</p><p>#!/bin/bash<br>VIDIR=$HOME/.vi<br>for a in $*<br>do<br>
<span class="substr"> </span>        f=`basename $a`<br>
        i=1<br>
        while [ -f $VIDIR/$f.$i ]</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64550433">

